  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want the chat bubbles large enough to comfortably fit longer writing and use the available space most effectively.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Improvement\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Improve the chat UX by better use of the screen real estate. Messages at present are too narrow and leave a lot of vacant space that could be better used to show additional content, enhancing information density especially on larger devices.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nBubbles should be capped at 320px max width, so they can't grow any wider than that. The larger margin should be at least 64px wide and it can grow larger if necessary but not smaller than that.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nBubbles are capped at 230px max width.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nAttached mockup with constraints\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1689\" alt=\"screenshot 2018-10-22 at 11 24 26\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/47286068-85968600-d5ed-11e8-9012-740e42c0344d.png\">\r\n\r\n",
